<br>
Americans do not want to live in a theocracy.  By and large, Americans believe that if it doesn't hurt other people you should be allowed to do it.<br>
<br>
While there very well may be things that are immoral that do not hurt other people, that is in my opinion a matter of personal morality and not the business of the government.  Government just needs to prevent us from infringing on the rights of others.  Achieving personal salvation for us is not the job of the government.<br>
<br>
