<br>
Drugs are another point where society has deemed them to be more troublesome than they are worth to have legal.  While you can argue that alcohol is a &quot;danger&quot; due to drunk driving, I can point out that unprotected anal sex is 100x more likely to transmit a Venereal disease.<br>
<br>
It's silly to use either of those as justifications to WHY we have the laws in the first place thou because they come into play but only as a justification to the people who are making the laws rather than the defining factors, that being how society feels.<br>
<br>
Suicide is illegal, yet it can quite easily be argued in the case of people who are terminally ill, that death is most definitely the pursuit of happiness.  Who's to say Sally's pursuit of happiness isn't swallowing a 12 gauge barrel and blowing her brains against the wall, yet we do it as a society and deem it to be &quot;wrong&quot; so we make it against the law. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204898"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.flash.net/~bigdon0/lfg.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1843<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/18/03 10:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ten Commandments Judge</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I can point out that unprotected anal sex is 100x more likely to transmit a Venereal disease<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes, but the risk is to the parties that make the choice to engage in the questionable behavior.  In drunk driving, the risk is to a 3rd party that did not consent to incur that risk.<br>
<br>
I do see your point though that many of our laws come indirectly out of religion as they represent consensus morals of a society, which if you trace back far enough, probably derive from religion.<br>
<br>
However, I believe that society is embracing a new paradigm.  I think it is decidedly secular and based on more philosophical ideas of morality such as utilitarianism.  We are increasingly tolerant as a society of most things that do not harm 3rd parties.<br>
