<br>
  There is no innate law that says you can not harm other people or do things that might remove personal possessions from the control of others, but rather our morals dictate to us that these things are indeed wrong.  It doesn't take a bible for someone to have moral character, but it does take strength of will to enforce those morals on yourself and to a greater extent to have the courage to enforce the majority belief on the populace as a whole.<br>
<br>
  I find it incredibly appalling that the judicial system of this country has taken it upon itself to override the actions of a state legislature.  Personally, if you don't like the law in the state of Texas, there are approximately 40 odd other states that will allow such behavior, and vice versa on various other laws.  It's not the Supreme Courts job to dictate what morals are ok to uphold and which are not in my opinion.  They are there to uphold the constitution of the United States and the Amendments.  <br>
